        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/28970",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=doctorrock83",
                        "name": "doctorrock83",
                        "displayName": "julien PAULI",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Agreed.\n\nI already told Zend (ralph probably) that a Zend_Db_Table_Select *should be given it's own table* in the from clause, just after creating it.\nIt's not logic to have a Zend_Db_Table_Select entirely empty at creation, it should at least contains its own table as its first from clause.\n\nSee :\n\n{code}\n\/\/ that's not logic\n$table->fetchall($table->select()->from($table, array('my', 'cols')));\n{code}\n\n{code}\n\/\/ that seems more logic\n$table->fetchall($table->select()->columns(array('my', 'cols')));\n{code}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=doctorrock83",
                        "name": "doctorrock83",
                        "displayName": "julien PAULI",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-02-20T05:29:03.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-02-20T05:29:03.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/29121",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=tech13",
                        "name": "tech13",
                        "displayName": "Michael Rehbein",
                        "active": false
                    },
                    "body": "Turns out just adding the from in the setTable doesn't act as expected.\n\n$select = $tbl->select()->columns('id'); would still include an all columns in the select.\n\n'select `table`.* , `table`.`id` from `table`'\n\nAttached is a patch I used to fix the bug for me.\n\nshort version:\nAdded a different version of the columns method for the class that includes the 'from' on demand.\nIf a column not from the primary table is requested, it will throw an error.\nSeemed logical since the assemble for Zend_Db_Table_Select would throw for any columns not in the primary table.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=tech13",
                        "name": "tech13",
                        "displayName": "Michael Rehbein",
                        "active": false
                    },
                    "created": "2009-02-26T10:27:28.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-02-26T10:27:28.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/29427",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=norm2782",
                        "name": "norm2782",
                        "displayName": "Jurrien Stutterheim",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "This issue is already known as ZF-3239. It's a tricky one and hard solve without BC issues. A real patch probably won't be available until ZF 2.0, where we can break the BC a bit. Although I would love to be proven wrong in this case ;)",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=norm2782",
                        "name": "norm2782",
                        "displayName": "Jurrien Stutterheim",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-03-11T20:29:47.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-03-11T20:29:47.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/33920",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ralph",
                        "name": "ralph",
                        "displayName": "Ralph Schindler",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Since 1.9 there has been a feature in place that allowed select() to be called on a table with that will load the from part into the object.\n\nPlease see [here|http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/manual\/en\/zend.db.table.html#zend.db.table.qry.rows.set.refine.example], and the api doc [here|http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/apidoc\/core\/Zend_Db\/Table\/Zend_Db_Table_Abstract.html#methodselect]\n\nI think it might fix this problem.\n\n-ralph",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ralph",
                        "name": "ralph",
                        "displayName": "Ralph Schindler",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-08-25T17:15:30.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-08-25T17:15:30.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/38650",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=tech13",
                        "name": "tech13",
                        "displayName": "Michael Rehbein",
                        "active": false
                    },
                    "body": "Was fixed as of 1.9.  Marking issue closed.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=tech13",
                        "name": "tech13",
                        "displayName": "Michael Rehbein",
                        "active": false
                    },
                    "created": "2010-02-22T11:02:44.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-02-22T11:02:44.000+0000"
                },
                {
